comment._content: This is Cape Reinga the Northern most tip of the North Island and is sacred to Maori www.doc.govt.nz/conservation/historic/by-region/northland... "Te Ika a Maui" is the Maori name for the North Island literally "The Fish of Maui" www.doc.govt.nz/getting-involved/volunteer-join-or-start-...
